definition: many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"

sentences.english: Here's a sample of other books in this Dover category.
sentences.chinese: 这里的样本其他书籍在这方面多佛尔港的类别。

sentences.english: The ferry that plies between dover and boulogne.
sentences.chinese: 定期往返于多佛和布伦之间的渡轮。

sentences.english: He hitchhiked to Dover and, towards evening.
sentences.chinese: 他搭便车到了多佛，天快黑时。

sentences.english: This ship runs between Dover and Calais.
sentences.chinese: 这条船来往于多佛与加来之间。

sentences.english: Somewhere on the east coast between Cromer and Dover.
sentences.chinese: 在东岸克罗默和多佛之间的某处。

sentences.english: Cathryn M. Delude is a freelance writer based in Andover, Mass.
sentences.chinese: 住在美国麻州安多佛的自由作家。

sentences.english: This bus goes to Dover beach.
sentences.chinese: 乘这辆公共汽车可抵达多佛尔海滩。

sentences.english: It would be somewhere on the east coast, probably between Cromer and Dover.
sentences.chinese: 而可能是东岸某处，也许在克罗默和多佛之间。

sentences.english: The narrowest part of the Channel is between Dover (in England) and Calais (in France). The two ports are twenty-two miles apart.
sentences.chinese: 海峡的最狭窄处在英国的多佛和法国的加莱之间。

sentences.english: The port of Dover is Englands gateway to Europe.
sentences.chinese: 多佛港是英国进入欧洲的大门。

sentences.english: The ship was sailing in the direction of Dover .
sentences.chinese: 轮船向多佛尔方向驶去。

sentences.english: But customs officers at Dover claimed it was being used for smuggling.
sentences.chinese: 但是多佛港口的海关官员却声称此车被用来走私。

sentences.english: The passengers and crew were brought off by the Dover lifeboat.
sentences.chinese: 乘客及船员都被多佛尔的救生艇救出。

sentences.english: She swam over the Strait of Dover.
Christopher Columbus wrote in his diary of this sea.
sentences.chinese: 克里斯多佛哥伦布在他的航海日记中写道。

sentences.english: After leaving Calais, the ship made for Dover.
sentences.chinese: 离开加来后，那艘船便驶往多佛。
